did.abstract: The Fundacion Eduardo Frei, Ano 2001 Proyecto Digitalizacion Archivo Historico is a joint digitization effort of the Fundacion Eduardo Frei, Santiago Chile and Stanford University Libraries. The electronic archive consists of digitized papers, monographs, memos, series, and audio / video clips documenting the Chilean presidency of Eduardo Frei.

accessrestrict.head: Access
accessrestrict.p: Access to the electronic files is available on a dedicated workstation in the Reading Room of Stanford University Libraries Department of Special Collections. Information regarding access to this electronic collection can be obtained by contacting the Department of Special Collections via email at speccollref@stanford.edu.

userestrict.head: Publication Rights
userestrict.p: Property rights reside with the repository. Literary rights reside with the creators of the documents or their heirs. To obtain permission to publish or reproduce, please contact the Public Services Librarian of the Dept. of Special Collections.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Fundacion Eduardo Frei, Ano 2001 Proyecto Digitalizacion Archivo Historico. Dept. of Special Collections, Stanford University Libraries, Stanford, Calif.

scopecontent.head: Collection Scope and Content Summary
scopecontent.p: The collection consist of seventy-six CD-ROMs and six Mini Digital Video Cassettes.

accessrestrict.p: Access to the electronic files is available on a dedicated workstation in the Reading Room of Stanford University Libraries Department of Special Collections. Information regarding access to this electronic collection can be obtained by contacting the Department of Special Collections at (650) 725-1022 or via email at speccoll@sulmail.stanford.edu.

scopecontent.p: Series 1 contains Tiff images of Eduardo Frei's presidental papers, memos, photographs, and associated monographs and publications.
